<%- include("partials/header") %>

<div class="container mt-5">
  <h1 class="mb-4 text-center">About This App</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    The <strong>Rain Forecast App</strong> is designed to help users quickly know if it will rain tomorrow in any city of their choice. 
    By leveraging real-time data from the <a href="https://openweathermap.org/" target="_blank">OpenWeatherMap API</a>, 
    the app provides a simple yes/no answer, making it practical for planning your day.
  </p>

  <h3 class="mt-4">Key Features</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Clean, intuitive interface</li>
    <li>Responsive design that works on mobile, tablet, and desktop</li>
    <li>Real-time weather forecast using OpenWeatherMap API</li>
    <li>Fast and lightweight for instant results</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="mt-4">How to Use</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to the Home page.</li>
    <li>Type the city you want to check.</li>
    <li>Click the "Check" button to see if it will rain tomorrow.</li>
    <li>Get a clear response instantly: <em>"Yes, it will rain"</em> or <em>"No, no rain tomorrow"</em>.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="mt-4">Technologies Used</h3>
  <p>
    This project is built using <strong>HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, JavaScript, Express.js, and EJS</strong>. 
    It demonstrates integration with a third-party API and server-side rendering.
  </p>

  <h3 class="mt-4">Credits</h3>
  <p>
    Weather data is provided by <a href="https://openweathermap.org/" target="_blank">OpenWeatherMap</a>. 
    This project is part of my portfolio capstone to showcase web development skills.
  </p>
</div>

